Hi, Ahammed.

As ahammed wrote to Dr. Math
On 08/29/2004 at 02:42:48 (Eastern Time),
>Dear sir, I have a wood 10m(metre)lenght,30cm(centimetre)width&10cm
>(centimetre)hight.what is the formula to find out cubic metre?how 
>much cubic metre are this? thank you sir

Is this a box shape -- all the faces are rectangles (all the angles 
are right angles)? If so, convert all dimensions to metres and 
multiply them together:

  length * width * height = volume
  10 m * 0.30 m * 0.10 m = 0.30 m^3 (cubic metres)

- Doctor Rick, The Math Forum
  <http://mathforum.org/dr.math/>

